emails.subject: Key Findings and Grades From CCData's April Exchange Benchmark
emails.body:
In April 2023, 15% of analysed exchanges were deemed to have inadequate KYC practices according to Ciphertrace. While this is in part due to the closure of poor, underperforming exchanges, it is an improvement from 21% in October 2022 and 35% in April 2022.
 
The number of Exchanges that possess an ISO 27001, SOC2 certificate, or similar, has increased from 24% in October 2022 to 30% in April 2023. 34% also employ the service of a  custody provider, increasing from 26% in October 2022.

emails.subject: Get a Masters degree in International Relations, Security, and Strategy
emails.body:
The Master of Arts in International Relations, Security, and Strategy from O.P. Jindal Global University has been designed to help students and working professionals from around the world open the door to a career path in the ever-expanding streams of civil and diplomatic services, conflict resolution, political journalism, international justice and international economic development.

By enrolling in this online degree, you will have the opportunity to learn from renowned International Relations academics, experts, and regional specialists who will bring their real-world experience to the virtual classroom.

emails.subject: Tech earnings, debt ceiling wrangling and GDP data ahead
emails.body: Investors are awaiting U.S. economic growth data, all while digesting results from Facebook owner Meta and looking ahead to Amazon's latest earnings. Elsewhere, House Republicans pass a new debt ceiling bill, but the political wrangling in Washington over the issue looks to be far from finished.
